Based on the 10-fold serial dilutions of genomic DNA or plasmid RNA, the limits of detection (Ct  ≤  37) were between 10 and 50 copies of nucleic acid per reaction depending on the assay. The coefficient of determination ( 
r2) between the Ct values and the copies of the nucleic acids per assay was above 0.99 for all assays. The qPCR efficiencies (E) ranged from 93% to 106% for Pneumo4B (Fig. 1
) and 91%–104% for Pneumo4 V (Fig. 2
).
